---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '~/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '~/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  locale="en"
  pageType="legal"
  path="privacy/"
  title="Privacy Policy – BBA GmbH | FBZ Waterstop Centering"
  description="GDPR privacy policy (Art. 13) for fugenblechzentrierung.de."
  noindex={true}
>
  <Header locale="en" minimal />
  <main id="main" class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="grid-frame">
      <article class="col-span-12 md:col-span-8 md:col-start-3 prose-measure">
        <span class="label-blue">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="mt-6 font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-ink-mute text-sm">Last updated: April 2026</p>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">1. Controller</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            The controller within the meaning of the GDPR and other national data protection laws of the member states as well as other data protection regulations is:
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            BBA GmbH<br />
            Silberberger Chaussee 14<br />
            15526 Bad Saarow, Germany<br />
            Phone: +49 33631 58374<br />
            Email: <a href="mailto:info@bba-badsaarow.de" class="underline decoration-ink-line hover:text-blue">info@bba-badsaarow.de</a>
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">Managing Director: Dr.-Ing. Jörn Budde</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">2. Data Protection Officer</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            The appointment of a data protection officer is not mandatory for us under § 38 para. 1 BDSG because fewer than 20 persons in our company are continuously involved in the automated processing of personal data. For privacy questions, please contact the address above.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">3. Hosting via Vercel</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            This website is hosted by Vercel Inc., 440 N Barranca Ave #4133, Covina, CA 91723, USA. Vercel is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework. We have additionally concluded a Data Processing Agreement (DPA) and EU Standard Contractual Clauses with Vercel.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            When you access our website, Vercel automatically records server log files that your browser transmits. These include, in particular:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc list-inside leading-relaxed space-y-1">
            <li>anonymised IP address</li>
            <li>date and time of access</li>
            <li>requested URL</li>
            <li>browser type and operating system</li>
            <li>referrer URL</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            These data serve exclusively to ensure trouble-free operation, threat detection, and technical optimisation. No merging with other data sources takes place.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Legal basis: Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in secure and efficient website operation).<br />
            Retention: server log files are deleted or anonymised after no more than 30 days.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">4. Fonts (self-hosted)</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            This website uses the typefaces “Clash Display" and “Satoshi", which are embedded locally on our server. There is <strong>no</strong> connection to external font-CDN services such as Google Fonts or Fontshare. No data is transmitted to third parties when the website is loaded.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">5. Cookies</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            This website uses <strong>no</strong> cookies — neither technically necessary nor optional. A consent banner is therefore not required.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">6. Analytics and tracking</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            This website uses <strong>no</strong> analytics or tracking services (such as Google Analytics, Vercel Analytics, Matomo, Plausible, Facebook Pixel, Sentry, or comparable tools). No user-based reach measurement takes place.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">7. Contact by email</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            If you contact us by email or via the “Request a quote" link, the data you provide (e.g. name, email address, message, and project information) will be stored by us for processing your inquiry and for possible follow-up questions.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Legal basis: Art. 6 para. 1 lit. b GDPR (initiation of a contractual relationship) or Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in answering inquiries).<br />
            Retention: until the processing of your inquiry is complete. Mandatory statutory retention obligations under German commercial and tax law (up to 10 years pursuant to § 257 HGB, § 147 AO) remain unaffected.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">8. SSL/TLS encryption</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            For security reasons, this website uses SSL/TLS encryption. You can recognise an encrypted connection by the lock symbol in your browser's address bar and by the address starting with “https://".
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">9. Transfer to third countries</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            A transfer of personal data to third countries takes place exclusively in the context of hosting by Vercel (USA). Vercel is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework, ensuring an adequate level of data protection. In addition, EU Standard Contractual Clauses pursuant to Art. 46 para. 2 lit. c GDPR have been agreed.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">10. Your rights as a data subject</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">You have the following rights with regard to personal data concerning you:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc list-inside leading-relaxed space-y-1">
            <li>Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to withdraw consent (Art. 7 para. 3 GDPR)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR). The competent supervisory authority for BBA GmbH is:
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Die Landesbeauftragte für den Datenschutz und für das Recht auf Akteneinsicht Brandenburg<br />
            Stahnsdorfer Damm 77<br />
            14532 Kleinmachnow, Germany<br />
            <a href="https://www.lda.brandenburg.de" class="underline decoration-ink-line hover:text-blue" rel="noopener" target="_blank">www.lda.brandenburg.de</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">11. Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR)</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Where personal data is processed on the basis of legitimate interests pursuant to Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR, you have the right to object to such processing. If you object, we will no longer process your personal data unless we can demonstrate compelling legitimate grounds for the processing that override your interests, rights, and freedoms. Please send your objection to <a href="mailto:info@bba-badsaarow.de" class="underline decoration-ink-line hover:text-blue">info@bba-badsaarow.de</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">12. Currency of this privacy policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            This privacy policy is currently valid and was last updated in April 2026. Due to the further development of our website or changing legal or regulatory requirements, it may become necessary to update this privacy policy.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer locale="en" />
</Layout>
